Government of Maharashtra
Department of Environment and Climate Change

Mantralaya, Mumbai 400032

Read: (1) Government Decision, Environment and Climate Change Department No. Mission-2022 / P.S. Preamble: The cash prizes and the procedure for appropriation of the prize money to the winning local bodies in the 5 groups of Majhi Vasundhara Abhiyan 2.0 has been notified vide Government Decision dated 5th December, 2022 at Reference No. (1). Accordingly, a Detailed Project Report of the works to be taken up by the local bodies out of the award amount has been prepared vide Government Decision dated 08.02.2022 at Reference No. Administrative approval has to be obtained from a committee headed by the Secretary, Department of Environment and Climate Change.

2. Accordingly, for grant of administrative approval to the Detailed Project Report received from the Awardee Local Bodies, Ms. The Committee has made recommendations after discussing the Detailed Project Report submitted by the Local Bodies in its meeting held on 02.05.2025 under the Chairmanship of Secretary, Department of Environment & Climate Change. It was under the consideration of the government to grant administrative approval to the Detailed Project Report of the respective local bodies as recommended by the committee.
The government's decision:

Considering the points mentioned in the Preamble, the total amount received by Mandrup Gram Panchayat under Maji Vasundhara Abhiyan 2.0 is Rs. The works to be taken up out of the prize money of 01.00 crore will cost Rs.

The Village Development Officer, Mandroop Gram Panchayat has submitted the proposal with the technical approval of the Executive Engineer, Zilla Parishad Solapur. The proposal was submitted by the Mandroop Gram Panchayat. The date of the Committee constituted under the Chairmanship of Secretary, Department of Environment and Climate Change was taken into consideration in its meeting held on 02.05.2025. As per the recommendations of the committee, a total of Rs. The works in the Detailed Project Report costing 1,00,02, 325.00 (Rupees One Crore Two Thousand Three Hundred and Twenty Five Only) are being accorded administrative sanction by the Government subject to the following conditions and conditions. The works for which administrative sanction is being granted are shown in the accompanying Annexure-I.
2. Terms and Conditions
1) Mandrup Gram Panchayat will be the operational mechanism for the works in this Detailed Project Report.

(2) The detailed project report shall be sent to my Vasundhara Mission Directorate by the 5th of every month, along with the physical progress report of the implementation of the works mentioned in this Detailed Project Report.
3) The implementation of the works in this Detailed Project Report should be completed within the next 6 months from the approval of the Administrator.
4) If the amount of the prize exceeds the amount, it should be made out of self-funding.
5) In case of any increase in the original project cost in this Detailed Project Report for any reason, no additional funds / grants will be made available for the same.

3. Under the Majhi Vasundhara Abhiyan, AST Gram Panchayat has been awarded the second position at the state level in the category of "Gram Panchayat Group (population more than 10 thousand)" at a cost of Rs. A prize money of ₹1. 00 crore has been received.

Out of the prize money of Rs. The first instalment of ₹1 lakh has been disbursed to them. Since the detailed project report of the works to be taken up out of this prize money has been accorded administrative sanction by the Government as per paragraph-1 above, the remaining amount of the prize money to the Mandrup Gram Panchayat is Rs. The Government is approving the disbursement of the second instalment of ₹1 lakh (Rupees fifty lakhs only) through the Maharashtra Pollution Control Board.
